claim: Flublok ensures identical antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected flu strains.
explanation: The image shows a table of contents for an MMWR report on influenza vaccine recommendations (listing sections like Introduction, Methods, Primary Changes and Updates, Recommendations for the Use of Influenza Vaccines, Influenza Vaccine Composition and Available Vaccines, etc.), along with CDC adoption of ACIP recommendations text and an editorial and production staff listing. The page contains only a contents list, ACIP adoption overview, and staff listings; it does not provide any information about Flublok or antigenic match with WHO- and FDA-selected strains, and therefore does not support the claim.
